node.text:
#ad I am so excited to be sharing this @VeraBradley backpack with you, because this back-to-school season, the brand is supporting @blessinginabackpack - with your help, Vera Bradley is making a $100K donation to further the nonprofit’s mission of providing food to elementary students who may otherwise go hungry. 

 As a teacher who has worked at a school where a majority of my students went home with bags of food on the weekend, this is an organization that is close to my heart. We all know we don’t stop worrying about or caring for our kids when they leave our classroom and I’m grateful organizations like Blessings in a Backpack exist to help students that may need it. 

 Shop Vera Bradley backpacks this year and know that you’re shopping with a purpose! #PackItWithPurpose

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Halee • Third Grade on June 22, 2021 tagging @harperkids, and @joinicanreadbookclub. May be an image of 2 people, book and text that says 'TCan Can comics Read! anRea an FISH and SUN SE'.

node.text:
#ad Did you know @HarperKids leveled I Can Read! books now have a new line of comics for emerging readers?! I had so much fun exploring 3 new titles and I can’t wait to add them to my classroom library this summer! 

I Can Read! Comics introduces emerging readers to the world of graphic novel storytelling (and feature some familiar #ICanRead characters). My students of all ages have always loved graphic novels and I love that I can now introduce them at an even earlier time and encourage that visual literacy. The comic format inspires reader engagement in a unique and inviting way. 

What are your favorite graphic novels and comics to include in your library? Be sure to check out the new #ICanReadComics and @JoinICanReadBookClub. I have a feeling they’ll be a hit in your classroom 😍

Visit the link in my stories to learn more 😊

node.text:
Are you a teacher looking to start or revamp your business this summer? ☀️💻💗 One of the first things you’ll need is a new logo and brand that perfectly represents you!!! Sound like you? I’ve got you covered! 🤩

I’m so excited to share that I’m reopening my logo shop this summer!!! Over the past 3 years I’ve worked with and designed for over 500 educators to create a brand they love. I absolutely love getting to flex my creative side and getting to know so many of you through logos! Designing brings me so much joy 🥰💻

My form will officially be open for the first time this summer on MONDAY, June 21st, at 10:00 am CST! Spots will be limited and I have a feeling they will go fast! 🤩⏰

Can’t wait to get back to connecting with you all. 😊 More info and examples of past work can be found at the link in my bio. I also have 2 huge logo highlights on my page full of logos I’ve done in the past! Feel free to send me any questions. 😊💗

Thank you @amberrcalderon for all your tips, help, and motivation! 💗 After you get your logo, be sure to visit her page for tips on how to continue growing your business, brand, store, or page! #teacherbusiness #teacherlogodesigners #teacherspayteachers

node.text:
Lookin’ a little bit more rough than I did the first day but WE DID ITTTTTT 👏🏼💗

One full year of in person teaching with a full class of the sweetest first graders 🥰💗 in the middle of a pandemic. 😷

We did it. I’m feeling all the feels today and I don’t even have the words, but thankfully I got the letter back that I wrote to myself at the beginning of the year today... 

“There will be a lot of unknowns and new things this year, but what can remain a constant despite all the uncertainly is love, relationships, and magic.” ✨ I’m proud of myself today because I feel as though I accomplished just that. This year was hard, no doubt, but it was also one of my best for a multitude of reasons and I will quite literally never forget this class. The bond we formed this year was different as we navigated all the new and challenging things together and I’ll always be grateful for that.

I’m proud of you too. Thanks for being on this journey with me 💗 Cheering for you no matter what stage you’re in - done, almost done, and stilllllll working. 🤟🏼 you got this. I know you do.

#lastdayofschool #getyourteachon #firstgradeteacher

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Halee • Third Grade on May 27, 2021 tagging @selfiewrldiowa. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
Guess who’s back … back again 😎

SURPRISE! 🥳💗 although, if you’ve been here awhile, this won’t come as a major shock 🤣 I’m going back to 3rd!!!!!!!

My time in 1st grade has been so fun and I am so beyond grateful for the lessons it taught me, but I’m ready to be back where I feel most confident and comfortable. 🤩 There’s just something about 3rd, you know? Can’t wait for ✨NEW✨ skip counting songs, all the multiplication & division my 💗 desires, and those deeper reading connections. 

LET’S 👏🏼 GO 👏🏼 Who’s excited?!? Thankfully staying at my same school that I love so much. Looking forward to building even more relationships and connections. 

(PS sorry for the unnecessary delay … teaching in a pandemic has me 😴 lol)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Halee • Third Grade on May 22, 2021 tagging @shop.callie.danielle. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
YOU CAN DO HARD THINGS! 💗

I had so much fun rocking this shirt my BFF @shop.callie.danielle designed yesterday with @chalk.and.coffee and all of YOU! 💗

You all remind me every day that we can do hard things. This year has been without a doubt one of the most challenging as we learned to navigate what education looked like in the middle of a pandemic and I’m SO PROUD OF YOU for showing up every day in new ways for yourself, your students, and your teammates. This wasn’t easy. This was hard. This was new. This was different. But we DID IT. We can do hard things. And we sure did 💛✨

Sending lots of love and relaxing vibes to you this weekend as we get ready to recharge for another week ahead.

What’s on your agenda for the weekend??? ⤵️ I have a whole lot of nothing on my schedule. Okay, maybe a @target run 😉 but otherwise nothing! 🤩 #teachersofinstagram #YCDHT #shopcalliedanielle #firstgrade

smiling but we’re close to tears 🥲🥲🥲🥲 (kidding lol)

It’s the final countdown friends!!!! We can do this!!! How many days do you have left?! 😍⤵️

I’ve said it before, but this has truly been one of the best years ever for me and I feel so so so grateful. I’m not looking forward to saying goodbye to this sweet class of kiddos ... but the future is looking bright 😎☀️ Moving on 🆙📦

#endoftheyear #firstgrade #teachersofinstagram
